The paper deals with numerical stability and accuracy of fast algorithms for matrix multiplication, which are primarily used in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper discusses algorithmic techniques for improving error guarantees. The paper also touches upon computational complexity (cs.CC) and scientific computing (cs.SC) in its discussion of practical applications.
